-- U.S. RESEARCH ROUNDUP-Bonanza Creek Energy, Northern Trust 
-- 
-- Fri May 23, 2014 02:30AM EDT
-- None



May 23 (Reuters) - Wall Street securities analysts revised their ratings and price targets on several U.S.-listed companies, including Bonanza Creek Energy and Northern Trust, on Friday.

HIGHLIGHTS * Bonanza Creek Energy <BCEI.N>: SocGen raises to buy from hold  * Northern Trust <NTRS.O>, BNY Mellon <BK.N>: Deutsche Bank starts with hold [ID:nWNBB04HHC]  Following is a summary of research actions on U.S. companies reported by Reuters on Friday. Stock entries are in alphabetical order. See bottom of the table for sector changes.   * 8X8 <EGHT.O>: B. Riley cuts target price to $8 from $10; rating neutral  * BNY Mellon <BK.N>: Deutsche Bank starts with hold rating  * Bonanza Creek Energy <BCEI.N>: SocGen raises to buy from hold  * Hess Corp <HES.N>: SocGen raises target price to $95 from $86; rating hold * Hess Corp <HES.N>: Global Hunter Securities raises target price to $91; neutral rating * Mentor Graphics <MENT.O>: Canaccord Genuity raises target to $27 from $25; rating buy * Northern Trust <NTRS.O>: Deutsche Bank starts with hold rating  * Perry Ellis International <PERY.O>: Keybanc raises target to $20 from $17; rating buy * Sanchez Energy <SN.N>: Canaccord Genuity raises target price to $41 from $36; rating  * Sanchez Energy <SN.N>: MLV Partners raises price target to $41; rating buy * State Street <STT.N>: Deutsche Bank starts with hold rating